3RD STRIKE

Bomb/Defuse Map for Counter-Strike: Source

CS:GO original map creator: Budfudlucker
CS:S map port creator: Niko
Navigation Mesh editor: Meurglis3

High-quality port for CS:S of the awesome same-named large-size map from CS:GO by Budfudlucker. This port combined the distinctive features from both versions of initial map - de_3rdstrike_b1 & de_3rdstrike, though contains some changes in comparison with the both original sources, which have been made for the maximum variability and intensity of a gameplay.

Story:
   At first the suicide bomber was driving the truck with explosive. The second there was an attempt of shelling with the mortars... After these two heavy attacks the Terrorists have to make this 3rd assault on the government missile site a success. If they lose the imminent missile launch will wipe their military training camp off the face of the Earth!

NOTE:
This map has simply a diabolical weight 666 Mb, also was compiled this a hellcat almost 13 hours... but it's worth it! Happy owners of Ryzen 7 and GTX 1080 - let enjoy to the fullest! Sad losers with Celeron and Radeon R5 - let them drool with envy :-)

P.S. ~ All good things come in threes :-)

Description: A small map composed of three rooms, stacked on top of one another . The room you spawn in, is kind of a tactical room with a tiny slit in the wall to shoot out of, also, there is a tunnel connecting ct spawn to t spawn.. and vice versa. You have a ladder next to you, where you can climb up or down.. Going down will take you to a neon blue bomb plant room filled with water (yes yes, a water bomb plant, pimp, I know), there are ledges for tactical camping lining the upper walls of the water room.  Up will lead you to a smoke filled, dark, red bomb plant zone. This is comprised of a catwalk and crates, and a fort, for cover. Both the catwalk and the ground are plantable.

The possible tactics of this map, the neon lighting, and just the sheer fun of this map is reason enough to give it a try.

Shout out to Heretique, Eksdee, and a huge thanks to Deadman-Sama, for helping me test the map in its pubescent stages and posing in screenshots.

This is a remake of the classic goldeneye/perfect dark map.  I added a few new parts to make the map more counter-strike friendly.  Let me know if these were good or bad ideas, and I will make changes as needed.  This was a fun map to make, got me plenty frustrated along the way though.  I remember playing this map all the time back on n64, I thought it would be fun to try to make it all from memory, I think in general I did a pretty good job with it...it's not 100% technically correct, but I hope you enjoy it anyways.  The map holds up to 40 players.  (note map is a bit brighter than these screen shots show).

The 2 bomb sites are located in the middle of the map, one on the second story, and the other on top story.  The glass is breakable but is hard to break.  There is also a basement, 2 sniper pits (but watch out there is a grate floor above you) and 2 other larger towers.

This is probably the only map I actually put time into and even then its not good because I'm still a beginner with hammer.

The doors dont show up in the screenshots but yes there are really doors in the doorways, all of them that I know of are functional.

A.I. don't really like the doors too much, they like to camp and get stuck in them and open and close them constantly so human players are probably a better idea, although you can still play with A.I. but they tend to follow the same strategy every round.

Hostages also have an issue with doors so you may have a hard time rescuing them but there are also 2 bomb zones on this map for the terrorist team to use but because of the maps layout people will probably end up killing each other before any team completes its objective.

Development of this map has not been stoped i still try to fix errors that I find and add in additional features.

The Second Instalment from my Aperture Experiment Series!
In this universe, Aperture science simulates combats in order to study the subjects (you and the bots). Each map is enclosed in a cube, where anyone who attempts to escape will certainly die! So fight for your survival and win! Winners get cake at the end!

There are two houses, a castle and a brick house. There are teleports (look for the blue light) that sends you to the enemy house, but be aware as you are for a second or two, you are vulnerable to be shot down while falling. You can also try to walk through the floating surfaces.

One bombsite, is very obvious, and its in the middle of the map.

There is a train constantly going from one house to the other

Remember to take cover, and watch out for those breakable walls

Up to 18 players
